   The only plus I see to the Coercer is that she will be wearing the kedge robe when she has it, so that is always a good thing.  Just take two groups to Kedge, kill Phin, go to Kith kill all the DEs, 13 hours after you killed Phin, go back to Kedge and clear the seahorses at about 13 hours 15 minutes after you killed phin, then pull any guardians that happen to spawn, then Phin will spawn about 13 and a half hours after you killed him.  Go back to Kith, wash, rinse, repeat.  Then if you just get mad, Kedge MQs go for 15k on Xegony, but finding someone you can trust is the hard part...But I have seen people offering RBGs for a MQ.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchantre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chantre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 11:13:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3359.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info Limbas - my problem is getting two groups organized and headed there before another group beats me.  The last 7 times we killed phinny, I think the drops were pretty rare, for all epics.  You had an awesome run of good luck I believe.  Hopefully mine will be too.<br>
